THE PILOT TRANSMITTED ON AN ADVISORY FREQUENCY 'CLEAR THE AREA I HAVE 
ENGINE TROUBLE'. WHILE TURNING FROM DOWNWIND TO THE BASE LEG OF HIS 
EMERGENCY APPROACH TO THE AIRPORT, WITNESSES OBSERVED THE AIRPLANE IN 
A STEEP RIGHT BANK WHEN IT SUDDENLY BANKED LEFT AND DESCENDED INTO 
THE GROUND. TEMPERATURE AND DEWPOINT WERE 54 DEGS AND 39 DEGS 
RESPECTIVELY. THESE TEMPS ARE CONDUCIVE TO THE FORMATION OF 
CARBURETOR ICE. 
